12. Calls for an international conference on Syria.

13. Reaffirms that Member States shall refrain from supporting non-State actors with nuclear, chemical, or biological weapons.

14. Demands non-State actors not develop or use such weapons.

15. Prohibits procurement of chemical weapons from Syria.

16. Threatens measures under Chapter VII in case of non-compliance.

17. Remains seized of the matter.
The Executive Council of the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) made a decision on the destruction of Syrian chemical weapons. The decision was made in response to concerns over the use of chemical weapons in the Syrian Arab Republic. Key points include: 

Recalling previous statements expressing deep concern over the possible use of chemical weapons in Syria and underlining that such use would be reprehensible; 
 Noting a UN report confirming the use of chemical weapons in the Ghouta area of Damascus on 21 August 2013; 
 Condemning the use of chemical weapons; 
 Welcoming a framework for the elimination of Syrian chemical weapons agreed by the US and Russian Federation; 
 Noting Syria's intention to apply the Chemical Weapons Convention provisionally and its subsequent accession to the Convention; 

The Council decided that the Syrian Arab Republic must: 
- submit further information on its chemical weapons within 7 days, including 
  - chemical names and military designators of each chemical in its stockpile 
  - quantities of chemicals and precursors 
  - toxins and quantities thereof.
The Security Council:

1. Decides that the Syrian Arab Republic shall:
(a) (i) provide detailed information on its chemical weapons programme, including research and development facilities, production facilities, and storage facilities;
(ii) provide specific type and quantities of munitions, sub-munitions, and devices in its chemical weapons stockpile;
(iii) provide geographic coordinates of all chemical weapons, storage facilities, production facilities, and research and development facilities;

(b) submit a declaration required by Article III of the Convention within 30 days;

(c) eliminate all chemical weapons material and equipment in the first half of 2014;

(d) destroy chemical weapons production and mixing/filling equipment by 1 November 2013;

(e) cooperate fully with the implementation of this decision, including providing unfettered access to OPCW personnel;

(f) designate a main point of contact for the Secretariat.
